\u043d\u0438\u0458\u0438|publisher=\u0418\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0440\u0438\u0458\u0441\u043a\u0438 \u0438\u043d\u0441\u0442\u0438\u0442\u0443\u0442 \u0421\u0420 \u0426\u0440\u043d\u0435 \u0413\u043e\u0440\u0435|location=Titograd|url=http://www.rastko.rs/rastko-al/zbornik1990/adraskovic-manjine_l.php|ref=harv}}\n**{{cite conference|last1=Laki\u0107|first1=Zoran|last2=\u017dugi\u0107|first2=Tomislav|title=\u041f\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0436\u0430\u0458 \u0458\u0443\u0433\u043e\u0441\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0435\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0445 \u043c\u0430\u045a\u0438\u043d\u0430 \u0443 \u0410\u043b\u0431\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0458\u0438 1945-1990|year=1991|origyear=1990|conference=\u0421\u0442\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432\u043d\u0438\u0448\u0442\u0432\u043e \u0441\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0435\u043d\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433 \u043f\u043e\u0440\u0438\u0458\u0435\u043a\u043b\u0430 \u0443 \u0410\u043b\u0431\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0458\u0438|publisher=\u0418\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0440\u0438\u0458\u0441\u043a\u0438 \u0438\u043d\u0441\u0442\u0438\u0442\u0443\u0442 \u0421\u0420 \u0426\u0440\u043d\u0435 \u0413\u043e\u0440\u0435|location=Titograd|url=http://www.rastko.rs/rastko-al/zbornik1990/zlakic-tzugic-manjine.php|ref=harv}}\n**{{cite conference|last=Markovi\u0107|first=Blagoje V.|title=\u0412\u0440\u0430\u043a\u0430 \u0438 \u0412\u0440\u0430\u0447\u0430\u043d\u0438|year=1991|origyear=1990|conference=\u0421\u0442\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432\u043d\u0438\u0448\u0442\u0432\u043e \u0441\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0435\u043d\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433 \u043f\u043e\u0440\u0438\u0458\u0435\u043a\u043b\u0430 \u0443 \u0410\u043b\u0431\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0458\u0438|publisher=\u0418\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0440\u0438\u0458\u0441\u043a\u0438 \u0438\u043d\u0441\u0442\u0438\u0442\u0443\u0442 \u0421\u0420 \u0426\u0440\u043d\u0435 \u0413\u043e\u0440\u0435|location=Titograd|url=http://www.rastko.rs/rastko-al/zbornik1990/bmarkovic-vraka.php|ref=harv}}\n**{{cite conference|last=\u0160\u0107epanovi\u0107|first=Slobodan|title=\u041d\u0430\u0458\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0458\u0438 \u0434\u0435\u043c\u043e\u0433\u0440\u0430\u0444\u0441\u043a\u0438 \u0438 \u0434\u0440\u0443\u0433\u0438 \u043f\u043e\u0434\u0430\u0446\u0438 \u043e \u0412\u0440\u0430\u043a\u0438|year=1991|origyear=1990|conference=\u0421\u0442\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432\u043d\u0438\u0448\u0442\u0432\u043e \u0441\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0435\u043d\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433 \u043f\u043e\u0440\u0438\u0458\u0435\u043a\u043b\u0430 \u0443 \u0410\u043b\u0431\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0458\u0438|publisher=\u0418\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0440\u0438\u0458\u0441\u043a\u0438 \u0438\u043d\u0441\u0442\u0438\u0442\u0443\u0442 \u0421\u0420 \u0426\u0440\u043d\u0435 \u0413\u043e\u0440\u0435|location=Titograd|url=http://www.rastko.rs/rastko-al/zbornik1990/sscepanovic-vraka.php|ref=harv}}\n**{{cite conference|last=Tomovi\u0107|first=Gordana|title=\u0410\u043b\u0442\u0438\u043d \u0443 XIV \u0438 XV \u0432\u0435\u043a\u0443|year=1991|origyear=1990|conference=\u0421\u0442\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432\u043d\u0438\u0448\u0442\u0432\u043e \u0441\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0435\u043d\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433 \u043f\u043e\u0440\u0438\u0458\u0435\u043a\u043b\u0430 \u0443 \u0410\u043b\u0431\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0458\u0438|publisher=\u0418\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0440\u0438\u0458\u0441\u043a\u0438 \u0438\u043d\u0441\u0442\u0438\u0442\u0443\u0442 \u0421\u0420 \u0426\u0440\u043d\u0435 \u0413\u043e\u0440\u0435|location=Titograd|url=http://www.rastko.rs/rastko-al/zbornik1990/gtomovic-altin.php|ref=harv}}\n**\u0418\u0437\u0432\u0435\u0448\u0442\u0430\u0458\u0438 \u0440\u0443\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433 \u043a\u043e\u043d\u0437\u0443\u043b\u0430 \u0418\u0432\u0430\u043d\u0430 \u0421\u0442\u0435\u043f\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447\u0430 \u0408\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0435\u0431\u043e\u0432\u0430 \u0438\u0437 \u0421\u043a\u0430\u0434\u0440\u0430 \u043e \u0441\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0435\u043d\u0441\u043a\u043e\u043c \u0436\u0438\u0432\u0459\u0443 \u0438 \u045a\u0438\u0445\u043e\u0432\u0438\u043c \u0446\u0440\u043a\u0432\u0430\u043c\u0430 \u0443 \u0410\u043b\u0431\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0458\u0438 \u0443 \u0434\u0440\u0443\u0433\u043e\u0458 \u043f\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0438\u043d\u0438 XIX \u0432\u0435\u043a\u0430\n**\u0421\u0440\u043f\u0441\u043a\u043e-\u043f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0430\u0432\u043d\u0430 \u0441\u043a\u0430\u0434\u0430\u0440\u0441\u043a\u0430 \u043e\u043f\u0448\u0442\u0438\u043d\u0430 \u0443 XIX \u0438 \u043f\u043e\u0447\u0435\u0442\u043a\u043e\u043c XX \u0432\u0435\u043a\u0430\n**\u0426\u0440\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e\u0440\u0441\u043a\u0430 \u0448\u0442\u0430\u043c\u043f\u0430 \u043e \u0441\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0435\u043d\u0441\u043a\u043e\u043c \u0441\u0442\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432\u043d\u0438\u0448\u0442\u0432\u0443 \u0443 \u0410\u043b\u0431\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0458\u0438 (1871-1918)\n**\u0421\u0440\u043f\u0441\u043a\u0435 \u0448\u043a\u043e\u043b\u0435 \u0443 \u0421\u043a\u0430\u0434\u0440\u0443 \u0438 \u0412\u0440\u0430\u043a\u0438 \u0438 \u0430\u043b\u0431\u0430\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0430 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0441\u0432\u0458\u0435\u0442\u043d\u0430 \u043f\u043e\u043b\u0438\u0442\u0438\u043a\u0430 \u0442\u0440\u0438\u0434\u0435\u0441\u0435\u0442\u0438\u0445 \u0433\u043e\u0434\u0438\u043d\u0430 XX \u0432\u0438\u0458\u0435\u043a\u0430\n**\u0426\u0440\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e\u0440\u0441\u043a\u0430 \u0448\u0442\u0430\u043c\u043f\u0430 \u043e \u0441\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0435\u043d\u0441\u043a\u043e\u043c \u0441\u0442\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432\u043d\u0438\u0448\u0442\u0432\u0443 \u0443 \u0410\u043b\u0431\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0458\u0438 1918-1938.\n**\u0421\u0440\u043f\u0441\u043a\u0435 \u0448\u043a\u043e\u043b\u0435 \u0443 \u0410\u043b\u0431\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0458\u0438\n**\u0408\u0443\u0433\u043e\u0441\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0435\u043d\u0441\u043a\u043e-\u0430\u043b\u0431\u0430\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0438 \u043e\u0434\u043d\u043e\u0441\u0438 1945-1948. \u0438 \u043d\u0430\u0448\u0435 \u043c\u0430\u045a\u0438\u043d\u0435 \u0443 \u041d\u0420 \u0410\u043b\u0431\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0458\u0438\n**\u041f\u0440\u0438\u0441\u0443\u0441\u0442\u0432\u043e \u043f\u0440\u0438\u043f\u0430\u0434\u043d\u0438\u043a\u0430 \u043d\u0430\u0440\u043e\u0434\u0430 \u0438\u0437 \u0426\u0440\u043d\u0435 \u0413\u043e\u0440\u0435 \u043d\u0430 \u0442\u043b\u0443 \u0410\u043b\u0431\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0458\u0435 \u0438 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0431\u043b\u0435\u043c\u0438 \u0434\u0432\u043e\u0432\u043b\u0430\u0441\u043d\u0438\u0447\u043a\u0438\u0445 \u0438\u043c\u0430\u045a\u0430 1945-1948. \u0433\u043e\u0434\u0438\u043d\u0435\n\n;Reports\n*{{cite journal|last=Xhaxho|first=M.|title=Minority Rights and the Republic of Albania: Missing the Implementation|publisher=lup.lub.lu.se|url=https://lup.lub.lu.se/luur/download?func=downloadFile&recordOId=1555225&fileOId=1563588}}\n*{{citation|title=Srpsko - albanski odnosi. Pogled iz Albanije|publisher=ISAC Fund|url=http://www.isac-fund.org/download/Srpsko-albanski_odnosi_-_Pogled_iz_Albanije.pdf}}\n\n== External links ==\n*[http://www.rastko.org.rs/rastko-al/index_l.php Projekat Rastko - Skadar]\n*[http://www.moraca-rozafa.org/ Association of the Serbo-Montenegrin minority in the Republic of Albania \"MORA\u010cA-ROZAFA\"]\n*{{citation|title=Kvadratura kruga: Kako su Srbi postali Albanci|url=http://www.rts.rs/page/tv/sr/story/20/RTS+1/795034/Kvadratura+kruga.html|publisher=RTS|location=Belgrade}} (Documentary in Serbian)\n*{{citation|title=Srbi u Albaniji|publisher=Vuji\u0107 televizija|location=Valjevo|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vTY5PacBQbk|quote=29 min.}} (Documentary in Serbian)\n*{{citation|title=Crno na bijelo - Kako zive Srbi u Albaniji|publisher=Radio Televizija BN|location=Bijeljina|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0vA2vx5kXdk}} (Emission in Serbian)\n\n{{Serbian diaspora}}\n{{ethnic groups in Albania}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Serb minority in Albania}}\n[[Category:Serb communities in Albania| ]]\n[[Category:Serb minorities|Albania]]\n[[Category:Montenegrin communities]]\n[[Category:Ethnic groups in Albania]]\n[[Category:Albania\u2013Serbia relations]]\n[[Category:Albanian people of Serb descent| ]]\n[[Category:Albanian people of Montenegrin descent| ]]\n[[Category:History of the Serbs]]\n[[Category:Serbian Orthodox Church in Albania]]\n", "name_user": "Maleschreiber", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Serbo-Montenegrins_in_Albania"}
{"title_page": "Walking on Sunshine (Katrina and the Waves song)", "text_new": "{{short description|1985 single by Katrina and the Waves}}\n{{About|the Katrina and the Waves song|other uses|Walking on Sunshine (disambiguation)}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Walking on Sunshine\n| cover      = Walkingonsunshine.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Katrina and the Waves]]\n| album      = [[Walking on Sunshine (Katrina and the Waves album)|Walking on Sunshine]]<br/>(''later version appeared on'' [[Katrina and the Waves (album)|Katrina and the Waves]])\n| released   =\n*26 April 1985\n*7 June 1996 (re-issue)\n| format     = [[Gramophone record|Record single]]\n| recorded   = 1983, 1985\n| studio     = Cambridge, England\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Pop rock]]<ref>{{cite web|first= Bruce |last= Eder |title= Katrina & the Waves \u2013 Artist Biography |publisher= AllMusic |accessdate= 24 January 2017 |quote= It peaked at number 28 in England and number 25 in America (the highest chart placement up to that time by any ex-member of the Soft Boys), and yielded the Top Ten U.S./U.K. hit \"Walking on Sunshine,\" one of the more memorable pop/rock songs of the decade. |url= http://www.allmusic.com/artist/katrina-the-waves-mn0000365542/biography}}</ref>\n| length     =\n*3:16 (original version)\n*4:00 (re-recorded version)\n| label      =\n*[[Attic Records (Canada)|Attic]]\n*[[Capitol Records|Capitol]]\n| writer     = [[Kimberley Rew]]\n| producer   = Katrina and the Waves, Pat Collier; [[Scott Litt]] (additional production)\n| prev_title = Plastic Man\n| prev_year  = 1984\n| next_title = Do You Want Crying\n| next_year  = 1985\n| misc       = {{Audio sample\n | type      = single\n | file      = Walking on Sunshine (Katrina and the Waves song).ogg\n}}\n{{External music video|{{YouTube|iPUmE-tne5U|\"Walking on Sunshine\u201d}}\n }}\n}}\n\n\"'''Walking on Sunshine'''\" is a song written by [[Kimberley Rew]] for [[Katrina and the Waves]]' 1983 [[Walking on Sunshine (Katrina and the Waves album)|eponymous debut full-length album]]. The re-recorded version was at first released on the band's [[1985 in music|1985]] [[Katrina and the Waves (album)|self-titled album]] as the album's second [[Single (music)|single]] and reached No. 4 in Australia, No. 9 in the United States, and No. 8 in the United Kingdom. It was the Waves' first US top 40 hit, and their biggest success in the United Kingdom until \"[[Love Shine a Light]]\" (1997). Originally conceived of as a ballad, Katrina Leskanich decided to belt the song out as a more upbeat song.<ref>{{cite web|title= Katrina Leskanich radio appearance |accessdate= 5 September 2010 |publisher= Stephaniemiller.com |url= http://www.stephaniemiller.com/}}</ref>\n\n==Success==\nRoyalties from airplay and advertisements of \"Walking on Sunshine\" have been extremely high. Katrina and the Waves kept the publishing rights and the royalties that typically go to the songwriter have been divided among the band members.{{clarify|date=August 2012}}<!--how'd they get away with that...?-->  Estimates are the song has earned $1 million per year for the ten years ending in 2010.{{citation needed|date=August 2012}} According to a former employee of [[EMI]], \"''Walking on Sunshine'' was the crown jewel in EMI's catalog,\" and that it was one of EMI's biggest earners from advertisers.<ref name=\"NPR\">{{cite web|first= Elizabeth |last= Blair |title= 'Walking On Sunshine': Living On A Song |publisher= [[NPR Music]] |accessdate= 24 May 2010 |url= https://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=127091908 |date= 24 May 2010}}</ref>\n\nIn late August and early September 2005, which marked the 20th anniversary of the song's release, the [[storm surge]] of a storm named [[Hurricane Katrina]] devastated much of the [[Gulf Coast of the United States|U.S. Gulf Coast]], and the [[MSNBC]] program ''[[Countdown with Keith Olbermann]]'' dubbed its coverage of the storm, \"Katrina and the Waves\"; the name also appeared in numerous headlines and [[blog]] postings. A ''[[The New York Times|New York Times]]'' reporter contacted [[Katrina Leskanich]], who said: \"The first time I opened the paper and saw 'Katrina kills 9,' it was a bit of a shock. ... I hope that the true spirit of 'Walking on Sunshine' will prevail. I would hate for the title to be tinged with sadness, and I will have to do my own part to help turn that around.\"<ref>{{cite news|first= Steven |last= McElroy |title= Arts, Briefly |newspaper= [[The New York Times]] |date= 1 September 2005 |accessdate= 9 September 2017 |url= https://www.nytimes.com/2005/09/01/arts/arts-briefly.html}}</ref> She also stated that she hoped that \"Walking on Sunshine\" would become an anthem for the Gulf Coast's recovery.<ref>{{cite news|first= Allen |last= Salkin |title= What's in a Name, Katrinas? |newspaper= [[The New York Times]] |date= 11 September 2005 |accessdate= 20 September 2017 |url= https://www.nytimes.com/2005/09/11/fashion/sundaystyles/whats-in-a-name-katrinas.html}}</ref>\n\n2010 was the 25th anniversary of the release of \"Walking on Sunshine,\" and a series of back-catalog re-releases and a re-recorded version of the track were released at the time.<ref>{{cite web|title= Kimberley Rew Celebrates 25th Anniversary of Walking On Sunshine With Four Retro Releases |publisher= antiMusic |url= http://www.antimusic.com/news/10/feb/03Kimberley_Rew_Celebrates_25th_Anniversary_of_Walking_On_Sunshine_With_Four_Retro_Releases.shtml |date= 2 March 2010 |accessdate= 13 March 2012}}</ref> A free download of one of the tracks from Kimberley Rew's solo album ''Bible of Bop'' was given away in March 2010 from the band's website.<ref>{{cite web|title= Katrina & The Waves |publisher= Katrinaandthewaves.net |accessdate= 3 March 2012 |url= http://www.katrinaandthewaves.net}}</ref>\n\nIn August 2015, which marked the 30th anniversary of the song's release, the song was acquired by [[BMG Rights Management]] for \u00a310 million, along with all the other songs written by Kimberley Rew and Katrina and the Waves.<ref>{{cite news|title= 'Walking on Sunshine' bought by BMG for \u00a310m |url= http://www.irishtimes.com/business/media-and-marketing/walking-on-sunshine-bought-by-bmg-for-10m-1.2307925 |newspaper= [[The Irish Times]] |date= 6 August 2015 |accessdate= 6 August 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Music video==\nThe music video opens with a [[London Docklands|Docklands]] alley, the Waves huddling whilst Katrina dances about above them. The video proceeds to depict the band performing live at a United Kingdom concert. Katrina herself is either with or not with them, but either dancing in a disused Docklands warehouse, or walking through [[Hyde Park, London|Hyde Park]] on a cloudy day, past a churchyard, [[Tower Bridge]], and the south bank of the Thames. She catches up with the others and feeds ducks (one of them eats the leftovers, referring to the Waves). The four all repair to a backstage dressing room and prepare for a concert.\n\n==Chart performance==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Weekly charts===\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Chart (1985)\n!Peak<br/>position\n|-\n|Australia ([[Kent Music Report]])<ref>{{cite journal|title= Hits of the World |magazine= [[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |date= 29 June 1985 |url= https://books.google.com?id=-iMEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PT54&dq=australia%22 |volume= 97 |issue= 26 |page= 62 |issn= 0006-2510}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|4\n|-\n{{singlechart|Canadaadultcontemporary|3|chartid=9317|accessdate=17 June 2013}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Canadatopsingles|3|chartid=0539|accessdate=17 June 2013}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Germany2|28|artist=Katrina And The Waves|song=Walking On Sunshine|songid=1275|accessdate=17 June 2013}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Ireland2|2|song=Walking on Sunshine|accessdate=17 June 2013}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|New Zealand|20|artist=Katrina And The Waves|song=Walking On Sunshine|accessdate=17 June 2013}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Sweden|12|artist=Katrina And The Waves|song=Walking On Sunshine|accessdate=17 June 2013}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Switzerland|14|artist=Katrina And The Waves|song=Walking On Sunshine|accessdate=17 June 2013}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|UK|8|date=1985-06-08|accessdate=17 June 2013}}\n|-\n|US ''Billboard'' [[Adult Contemporary (chart)|Adult Contemporary]]<ref name=\"awards\"/>\n|align=\"center\"|21\n|-\n|US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]]<ref name=\"awards\">{{cite web|title= Katrina & the Waves \u2013 Awards |publisher= [[AllMusic]]. [[All Media Network]] |url= http://www.allmusic.com/artist/katrina-the-waves-mn0000365542/awards |accessdate= 17 June 2013}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|9\n|-\n|US ''Billboard'' [[Dance Club Songs|Hot Dance Club Play]]<ref name=\"awards\"/>\n|align=\"center\"|19\n|-\n|US ''Billboard'' [[Mainstream Rock (chart)|Top Rock Tracks]]<ref name=\"awards\"/>\n|align=\"center\"|21\n|-\n|US ''[[Cashbox (magazine)|Cash Box]]''<ref>{{cite web|url= http://cashboxmagazine.com/archives/80s_files/19850615.html |title= CASH BOX Top 100 Singles \u2013 Week ending JUNE 15, 1985 |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20120918030111/http://cashboxmagazine.com/archives/80s_files/19850615.html |archivedate= 18 September 2012}}. ''[[Cashbox (magazine)|Cash Box]]''.</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|9\n|}\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n!Chart (1996)\n!Peak<br/>position\n|-\n{{singlechart|UK|53|artist=Katrina & the Waves|song=Walking on Sunshine|date=19960602|accessdate=12 July 2014|refname=UK1996}}\n|}\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n!Chart (2017)\n!Peak<br/>position\n|-\n{{singlechart|Poland|84|chartid=2456|year=2017|accessdate=2 October 2017}}\n|}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Year-end charts===\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Chart (1985)\n!Position\n|-\n|Australia ([[Kent Music Report]])<ref>{{cite web|title= Forum \u2013 ARIA Charts: Special Occasion Charts \u2013 Top 100 End of Year AMR Charts \u2013 1980s |publisher= Australian-charts.com. Hung Medien |url= http://australian-charts.com/forum.asp?todo=viewthread&id=40275 |accessdate= 12 July 2014}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|21\n|-\n|Canada ([[RPM (magazine)|''RPM'' Top 100 Singles]])<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.collectionscanada.gc.ca/rpm/028020-119.01-e.php?&file_num=nlc008388.0619&type=1&interval=20&PHPSESSID=u9874ano8k0c5b6bkp4r8qrbp3 |title= Top Singles \u2013 Volume 43, No. 16, December 28 1985 |work= [[RPM (magazine)|RPM]] |publisher= [[Library and Archives Canada]] |accessdate= 12 July 2014}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|18\n|-\n|US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]]<ref>{{cite web|title= Top 100 Hits for 1985 |publisher= The Longbored Surfer |accessdate= 12 July 2014 |url= http://longboredsurfer.com/charts/1985.php}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|75\n|-\n|US [[Cashbox (magazine)|''Cash Box'']]<ref>{{cite web|url= http://cashboxmagazine.com/archives/80s_files/1985YESP.html |title= The CASH BOX Year-End Charts: 1985 |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20121001214739/http://cashboxmagazine.com/archives/80s_files/1985YESP.html |archivedate= 1 October 2012}}. ''[[Cashbox (magazine)|Cash Box]]''.</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|80\n|}\n{{col-end}}\n\n===Certifications===\n{{Certification Table Top}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|type=single|region=Canada|artist=Katrina and the Waves|title=Walking on sunshine|award=Gold|digital=true|certyear=1985|relyear=1985|accessdate=22 June 2018}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|type=single|region=Denmark|artist=Katrina & the Waves|title=Walking on Sunshine|award=Gold|certyear=2019|relyear=1985|id=8457|accessdate=21 September 2019}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|type=single|region=Italy|artist=Katrina & the Waves|title=Walking on Sunshine|award=Gold|certyear=2018|relyear=1985|accessdate=3 September 2018}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|type=single|region=United Kingdom|artist=Katrina & the Waves|title=Walking on Sunshine|award=Platinum|certyear=2020|relyear=2005|id=13370-4062-1|accessdate=11 January 2020}}\n{{Certification Table Bottom|streaming=true}}\n\n==Dolly Parton version==\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Walking on Sunshine\n| cover      = DollyWalkingOnSunshine.jpeg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Dolly Parton]]\n| album      = [[Treasures (Dolly Parton album)|Treasures]]\n| released   = 1999\n| format     = [[Maxi single]]\n| recorded   =\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      =\n| length     = 3:12\n| label      =\n*Rising Tide\n*Blue Eye\n| writer     = [[Kimberley Rew]]\n| producer   =\n| prev_title = [[Just When I Needed You Most]]\n| prev_year  = 1996\n| next_title = Peace Train\n| next_year  = 1997\n}}\n\nIn 1996, [[Dolly Parton]] included a version of \"Walking on Sunshine\" on her album of covers, ''[[Treasures (Dolly Parton album)|Treasures]],'' stating in interviews to promote the album, as well as her [[CBS]] TV special to promote the album, that she had long loved the song. In 1997, a dance remix of Parton's version was released.\n\n{{clear}}\n\n==Aly & AJ cover==\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Walking on Sunshine\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Aly & AJ]]\n| album      = [[Into the Rush]] and [[Herbie: Fully Loaded#Soundtrack|Herbie: Fully Loaded soundtrack]]\n| released   = 2005\n| format     = [[Radio Disney]] single\n| recorded   =\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      =\n| length     = 3:54\n| label      = [[Hollywood Records]]\n| writer     = [[Kimberley Rew]]\n| producer   = [[Matthew Gerrard]]\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year  =\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n}}\n[[Matthew Gerrard]] produced a cover of \"Walking on Sunshine\" for American [[pop rock]] duo [[Aly & AJ]]'s debut album, ''[[Into the Rush]]''. The song was released as the album's fourth single on June 22, 2005 (see [[2005 in music]]). It was also used to promote the film ''[[Herbie: Fully Loaded]]'' and makes an appearance on the [[Herbie: Fully Loaded (soundtrack)|movie soundtrack]]. The single's video features Aly & AJ performing and is intercut with clips from the film ''Herbie: Fully Loaded''. The song was shortened down to one minute and 55 seconds (1:55), as it is used for the video. This song was also featured in the 2010 film ''[[Ramona and Beezus]]'' and the 2011 film ''[[Sharpay's Fabulous Adventure]]''.\n\n===Track listings===\n{{Track listing\n| headline        = Radio Disney Promo CD<ref>{{cite web|title= Walking on Sunshine ~ Release by Aly & AJ |publisher= [[MusicBrainz]] |accessdate= 12 July 2014 |url= http://musicbrainz.org/release/56710ef6-6aa7-4c40-a69b-173409acdd75}}</ref>\n| title1          = Walking on Sunshine\n| writer1         = Kimberly Rew\n| length1         = 3:54\n}}\n\n===Release history===\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n!Date\n!Country\n!Format\n!Label\n|-\n|22 June 2005\n|United States\n|rowspan=\"2\"|Promo CD\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Hollywood Records]]\n|}\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n!Date\n!Country\n!Format\n!Label\n|-\n|6 February 2006\n|United Kingdom\n|rowspan=\"2\"|Promo CD\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Squirrel Records]]\n|}\n\n{{clear}}\n\n==Appearances in popular culture==\n<!-- None of the individual sightings are sourced. Please don't add more without including a source; and if you have a real source (not IMDB, which is reader-populated like Wikipedia) for any already here, please add. -->\nThe song is very popular in commercials, and advertisers typically pay $150,000 to $200,000 per year to use the song.<ref name=\"NPR\"/>\n* In September 2010, the cast of ''[[Ni Hao, Kai-Lan]]'' and [[Colbie Callat]] cpveed the song as part of the ''Nickelodeon/NOGGIN Mega Music Festival''. The animation was released separately on select Nick Jr DVDs and a few Nick Jr commercial break airtimes.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{MetroLyrics song|aly-aj|walking-on-sunshine|version=Aly & AJ version}}<!-- Licensed lyrics provider -->\n\n{{Katrina and the Waves}}\n{{78violet}}\n\n[[Category:1983 songs]]\n[[Category:1985 singles]]\n[[Category:1997 singles]]\n[[Category:2005 singles]]\n[[Category:Katrina and the Waves songs]]\n[[Category:Aly & AJ songs]]\n[[Category:Capitol Records singles]]\n[[Category:Hollywood Records singles]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Kimberley Rew]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|1985 single by Katrina and the Waves}}\n{{About|the Katrina and the Waves song|other uses|Walking on Sunshine (disambiguation)}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Walking on Sunshine\n| cover      = Walkingonsunshine.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Katrina and the Waves]]\n| album      = [[Walking on Sunshine (Katrina and the Waves album)|Walking on Sunshine]]<br/>(''later version appeared on'' [[Katrina and the Waves (album)|Katrina and the Waves]])\n| released   =\n*26 April 1985\n*7 June 1996 (re-issue)\n| format     = [[Gramophone record|Record single]]\n| recorded   = 1983, 1985\n| studio     = Cambridge, England\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Pop rock]]<ref>{{cite web|first= Bruce |last= Eder |title= Katrina & the Waves \u2013 Artist Biography |publisher= AllMusic |accessdate= 24 January 2017 |quote= It peaked at number 28 in England and number 25 in America (the highest chart placement up to that time by any ex-member of the Soft Boys), and yielded the Top Ten U.S./U.K. hit \"Walking on Sunshine,\" one of the more memorable pop/rock songs of the decade. |url= http://www.allmusic.com/artist/katrina-the-waves-mn0000365542/biography}}</ref>\n| length     =\n*3:16 (original version)\n*4:00 (re-recorded version)\n| label      =\n*[[Attic Records (Canada)|Attic]]\n*[[Capitol Records|Capitol]]\n| writer     = [[Kimberley Rew]]\n| producer   = Katrina and the Waves, Pat Collier; [[Scott Litt]] (additional production)\n| prev_title = Plastic Man\n| prev_year  = 1984\n| next_title = Do You Want Crying\n| next_year  = 1985\n| misc       = {{Audio sample\n | type      = single\n | file      = Walking on Sunshine (Katrina and the Waves song).ogg\n}}\n{{External music video|{{YouTube|iPUmE-tne5U|\"Walking on Sunshine\u201d}}\n }}\n}}\n\n\"'''Walking on Sunshine'''\" is a song written by [[Kimberley Rew]] for [[Katrina and the Waves]]' 1983 [[Walking on Sunshine (Katrina and the Waves album)|eponymous debut full-length album]]. The re-recorded version was at first released on the band's [[1985 in music|1985]] [[Katrina and the Waves (album)|self-titled album]] as the album's second [[Single (music)|single]] and reached No. 4 in Australia, No. 9 in the United States, and No. 8 in the United Kingdom. It was the Waves' first US top 40 hit, and their biggest success in the United Kingdom until \"[[Love Shine a Light]]\" (1997). Originally conceived of as a ballad, Katrina Leskanich decided to belt the song out as a more upbeat song.<ref>{{cite web|title= Katrina Leskanich radio appearance |accessdate= 5 September 2010 |publisher= Stephaniemiller.com |url= http://www.stephaniemiller.com/}}</ref>\n\n==Success==\nRoyalties from airplay and advertisements of \"Walking on Sunshine\" have been extremely high. Katrina and the Waves kept the publishing rights and the royalties that typically go to the songwriter have been divided among the band members.{{clarify|date=August 2012}}<!--how'd they get away with that...?-->  Estimates are the song has earned $1 million per year for the ten years ending in 2010.{{citation needed|date=August 2012}} According to a former employee of [[EMI]], \"''Walking on Sunshine'' was the crown jewel in EMI's catalog,\" and that it was one of EMI's biggest earners from advertisers.<ref name=\"NPR\">{{cite web|first= Elizabeth |last= Blair |title= 'Walking On Sunshine': Living On A Song |publisher= [[NPR Music]] |accessdate= 24 May 2010 |url= https://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=127091908 |date= 24 May 2010}}</ref>\n\nIn late August and early September 2005, which marked the 20th anniversary of the song's release, the [[storm surge]] of a storm named [[Hurricane Katrina]] devastated much of the [[Gulf Coast of the United States|U.S. Gulf Coast]], and the [[MSNBC]] program ''[[Countdown with Keith Olbermann]]'' dubbed its coverage of the storm, \"Katrina and the Waves\"; the name also appeared in numerous headlines and [[blog]] postings. A ''[[The New York Times|New York Times]]'' reporter contacted [[Katrina Leskanich]], who said: \"The first time I opened the paper and saw 'Katrina kills 9,' it was a bit of a shock. ... I hope that the true spirit of 'Walking on Sunshine' will prevail. I would hate for the title to be tinged with sadness, and I will have to do my own part to help turn that around.\"<ref>{{cite news|first= Steven |last= McElroy |title= Arts, Briefly |newspaper= [[The New York Times]] |date= 1 September 2005 |accessdate= 9 September 2017 |url= https://www.nytimes.com/2005/09/01/arts/arts-briefly.html}}</ref> She also stated that she hoped that \"Walking on Sunshine\" would become an anthem for the Gulf Coast's recovery.<ref>{{cite news|first= Allen |last= Salkin |title= What's in a Name, Katrinas? |newspaper= [[The New York Times]] |date= 11 September 2005 |accessdate= 20 September 2017 |url= https://www.nytimes.com/2005/09/11/fashion/sundaystyles/whats-in-a-name-katrinas.html}}</ref>\n\n2010 was the 25th anniversary of the release of \"Walking on Sunshine,\" and a series of back-catalog re-releases and a re-recorded version of the track were released at the time.<ref>{{cite web|title= Kimberley Rew Celebrates 25th Anniversary of Walking On Sunshine With Four Retro Releases |publisher= antiMusic |url= http://www.antimusic.com/news/10/feb/03Kimberley_Rew_Celebrates_25th_Anniversary_of_Walking_On_Sunshine_With_Four_Retro_Releases.shtml |date= 2 March 2010 |accessdate= 13 March 2012}}</ref> A free download of one of the tracks from Kimberley Rew's solo album ''Bible of Bop'' was given away in March 2010 from the band's website.<ref>{{cite web|title= Katrina & The Waves |publisher= Katrinaandthewaves.net |accessdate= 3 March 2012 |url= http://www.katrinaandthewaves.net}}</ref>\n\nIn August 2015, which marked the 30th anniversary of the song's release, the song was acquired by [[BMG Rights Management]] for \u00a310 million, along with all the other songs written by Kimberley Rew and Katrina and the Waves.<ref>{{cite news|title= 'Walking on Sunshine' bought by BMG for \u00a310m |url= http://www.irishtimes.com/business/media-and-marketing/walking-on-sunshine-bought-by-bmg-for-10m-1.2307925 |newspaper= [[The Irish Times]] |date= 6 August 2015 |accessdate= 6 August 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Music video==\nThe music video opens with a [[London Docklands|Docklands]] alley, the Waves huddling whilst Katrina dances about above them. The video proceeds to depict the band performing live at a United Kingdom concert. Katrina herself is either with or not with them, but either dancing in a disused Docklands warehouse, or walking through [[Hyde Park, London|Hyde Park]] on a cloudy day, past a churchyard, [[Tower Bridge]], and the south bank of the Thames. She catches up with the others and feeds ducks (one of them eats the leftovers, referring to the Waves). The four all repair to a backstage dressing room and prepare for a concert.\n\n==Chart performance==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Weekly charts===\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Chart (1985)\n!Peak<br/>position\n|-\n|Australia ([[Kent Music Report]])<ref>{{cite journal|title= Hits of the World |magazine= [[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |date= 29 June 1985 |url= https://books.google.com?id=-iMEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PT54&dq=australia%22 |volume= 97 |issue= 26 |page= 62 |issn= 0006-2510}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|4\n|-\n{{singlechart|Canadaadultcontemporary|3|chartid=9317|accessdate=17 June 2013}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Canadatopsingles|3|chartid=0539|accessdate=17 June 2013}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Germany2|28|artist=Katrina And The Waves|song=Walking On Sunshine|songid=1275|accessdate=17 June 2013}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Ireland2|2|song=Walking on Sunshine|accessdate=17 June 2013}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|New Zealand|20|artist=Katrina And The Waves|song=Walking On Sunshine|accessdate=17 June 2013}}\n|-\n{{s